Yea, I do tend to stick to "tuple structs" or "tuple variants" in `enums` longer than I used to. I wouldn't worry about converting it from a tuple to a full struct until/unless you get two similarly-typed fields which might be confused for one another. A comment above the variant is fine.

Note also though that you can do:
```rust
enum SomeEnum {
    NoData,
    SomeData {
      data: Vec<(String,String)>,
    },
}
```
...which can be a bit easier than defining a newtype iff you don't actually ever need to use the newtype outside the context of the enum.

